        "body": "## Summary\n- Fix classification: Root-cause fix.\n- Maintainer-ready confidence: High.\n- Root cause: The duplicate `💬` commentary note came from a projector state invariant violation: Codex app-server emits the same assistant commentary text through two upstream notification lanes, typed `agentMessage` events and raw `rawResponseItem/completed` events, but OpenClaw keyed commentary progress identity only by the lane-specific item id; because the typed and raw lanes use different ids for the same commentary note, downstream dispatch received two independent preamble items and flushed both as separate Discord progress messages.\n- Why this is root-cause fix: The fix restores the projector-level commentary identity invariant before channel delivery by deduping adjacent cross-lane mirrors with different item ids and equivalent normalized text, including the raw-first lifecycle where the raw lane has the complete text and typed `agentMessage` later arrives as chunked deltas; this addresses the source event projection boundary that caused the duplicate, instead of adding a Discord-only suppression workaround after the duplicate item events already exist.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts`; `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts -t commentary`.\n- Observed result after fix: Projector regression tests passed for typed-first, raw-first, and raw-first chunked typed-delta lane mirrors, and downstream commentary dispatch validation passed.\n- What did NOT change: Only Codex app-server commentary progress projection is changed; final-answer resolution, non-commentary assistant streaming, raw assistant text collection, same-item commentary progress updates, and channel dispatch buffering are unchanged.\n- What problem does this PR solve? It prevents duplicate Discord `💬` commentary progress messages for one Codex app-server verbose-mode commentary note.\n- What is the intended outcome? A single commentary note mirrored by Codex typed and raw lanes becomes one OpenClaw progress event.\n- What should reviewers focus on? The cross-lane dedupe conditions in the Codex event projector and the raw-first chunked delta regression coverage.\n\n## Linked context\n- Fixes #93296.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Duplicate `💬` commentary notes from Codex app-server verbose-mode typed/raw lane mirrors.\n- Real environment tested: OpenClaw Codex app-server projector and auto-reply commentary dispatch unit tests, including extension-specific validation for `extensions/codex`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts`\n- Exit code: 0\n- Evidence after fix: Copied terminal output from the projector validation run:\n```text\nRUN  v4.1.7 [redacted-local-path]\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  93 passed (93)\n```\n- Observed result after fix: Projector coverage passes for commentary progress streaming plus typed-first, raw-first, and raw-first chunked typed-delta dedupe cases.\n- What was not tested: Live Discord delivery was not available in this environment, so no live Discord message was sent; local validation completed with the projector and downstream dispatch tests passing.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: Validation is unit-level coverage of the projector and downstream dispatch behavior using the existing Vitest harness.\n\n## Tests and validation\n- Extension-specific validation: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/event-projector.test.ts`\n  ```text\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n       Tests  93 passed (93)\n  ```\n- Downstream commentary dispatch validation: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts -t commentary`\n  ```text\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n       Tests  6 passed | 203 skipped (209)\n  ```\n- Regression coverage: typed-first mirror dedupe, raw-first mirror dedupe, raw-first with chunked typed deltas, existing commentary streaming, and downstream commentary dispatch buffering.\n\n## Risk checklist\n- Highest risk area: Over-deduping legitimate commentary progress updates.\n- Mitigation: The dedupe is limited to adjacent cross-lane mirrors with different item ids, while same-lane same-item progress updates still use the existing per-item snapshot behavior. The existing commentary streaming test still expects incremental same-item updates.\n\n## Current review state\n- Local Codex diff review completed without findings after the chunked raw-first case was added.\n",
